Within 30 days of District's issuance of the  Permit to Operate for Applic ation 14886 or 
the completion of the sour gas pipeline upgrade project at or between S -4252, S -4253, S -
4348, and S -4435, the Owner/Operator shall provide the District’s Engineering Division 
with a final count of all fugitive components and each component’s  unique permanent 
identification codes in this project.  The owner/operator has been permitted to install the 
following fugitive components:  

154 valves in hydrocarbon service ; 
5 pressure relief valves in hydrocarbon service;  
257 flanges in hydrocarbon se rvice;  
46 valves in stripped water service;  
1 pump in stripped water service;  
